1 AN ACT relating to interment at state veterans' cemeteries.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 40.315 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) The Department of Veterans' Affairs shall establish and maintain state veterans'
5 cemeteries in the Commonwealth for the purpose of providing for the interment of
6 veterans of the[ United States] Armed Forces of the United States and for their
7 eligible next of kin, as determined by the department.
8 (2) Eligibility for interment at a Kentucky state veterans' cemetery shall include:
9 (a) Persons who are eligible for interment in a veterans' national cemetery
10 pursuant to 38 U.S.C. sec. 2402 and regulations promulgated thereunder;
11 and
12 (b) Any member of a reserve component of the Armed Forces, the Army
13 National Guard, or the Air National Guard not otherwise qualified in
14 paragraph (a) of this subsection, if:
15 1. The member completed the initial period of service as required by 10
16 U.S.C. sec. 651(a) and was discharged under conditions other than
17 dishonorable; or
18 2. The member of the Army National Guard or the Air National Guard
19 died while on state active duty or while serving under Title 32 of the
20 United States Code.
21 (3) For a person eligible under subsection (2)(b) of this section, the eligibility for
22 interment of the person's spouse, surviving spouse, minor child, and dependent
23 incapacitated child shall be determined pursuant to 38 U.S.C. sec. 2402(a)(5).
24 (4) The Kentucky state veterans' cemeteries shall be under the administrative authority
25 and control of the Department of Veterans' Affairs. The department[ of Veterans'
26 Affairs] may promulgate administrative regulations necessary to operate the
27 cemeteries in compliance with applicable state and federal statutes and regulations.
